        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 4:40PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles southwest of Balmorhea State Park to 10
miles northwest of McDonald Observatory. Movement was northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buffalo Trail Scout Camp and Black Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
